Use tidyr::uncount() to convert our lobstor data from frequency format to case format

lobster_tidy <- lobster_abundance %>% 
  uncount(lobster_count)

Convert the date column to class Date

Well use the lubridate package to convert to Date format, and then to help us easily parse month & year

lobster_date = lobster_tidy %>% 
  mutate(date_new = lubridate::mdy(date))

Now lets parse month year using lubridate::month lubridate::year

lobster_parse_data <- lobster_date %>% 
  mutate(
    obs_month = lubridate::month(date_new, label = TRUE), 
    obs_year = lubridate::year(date_new)
  )

New lets find counts of lobsters based on different hirerarchical grouping:

first lets counts lobstrs by year and month

lobster_yr <- lobster_parse_data %>%
  count(obs_month, obs_year)

lobster_y <- lobster_parse_data %>% 
  count(obs_year)

lobster_site <-  lobster_parse_data %>% 
  count(site)

# tidy data every obs has its own row, we can decide how to group data

If we want to create a summary table contains statistics OTHER than counts by group, its easier to use group_by() + n()

lobster_summary <- lobster_parse_data %>% 
  group_by(site) %>% 
  summarize(
    mean_size = mean(size_mm, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_size = sd(size_mm, na.rm = TRUE),
    lobster_num = n()
  )

lobster_summary
## # A tibble: 5 x 4
##   site  mean_size sd_size lobster_num

Find CI

Use t.test() to find CI and perform t-test to compare means of two samples

ivee_lobster <- lobster_tidy %>% 
  filter(site == "IVEE") %>% 
  pull(size_mm)
t.test(ivee_lobster)
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  ivee_lobster
## t = 245.23, df = 2302, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  72.99130 74.16806
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##  73.57968

Two sample t-test to compare means

We want to ask is there is any sig diff in lobster lengths at Naples, and Mohawk reafs?

weve done our necessary exploratory analysis to determine that a 2-sample t-test for means comparison is approprate.

napl_sample <- lobster_tidy %>% 
  filter(site == "NAPL") %>% 
  pull("size_mm")

mohk_sample <- lobster_tidy %>% 
  filter(site == "MOHK") %>% 
  pull("size_mm")

mn_ttest <- t.test(mohk_sample, napl_sample)
mn_ttest
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  mohk_sample and napl_sample
## t = -19.849, df = 1850.8, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -12.43436 -10.19806
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  66.86833  78.18454

there is a sig diff in lobs lengths between Napl, and Mahk

lobster_mn <- lobster_tidy %>% 
  filter(site %in% c("NAPL", "MOHK"))

mn_ttest2 <- t.test(size_mm ~ site, data = lobster_mn)
mn_ttest2
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  size_mm by site
## t = -19.849, df = 1850.8, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -12.43436 -10.19806
## sample estimates:
## mean in group MOHK mean in group NAPL 
##           66.86833           78.18454

Here is the p value : 1.215407810^{-79}

Here is the t statistics: -19.8487322
